        "end_card_button_label_mobile": "",
        "transcript": "Setting: A lush green garden and a bright, sunlit studio filled with fashion sketches and colorful fabrics.\n\n[Visual Description]: The video opens with Anjelica Roselyn walking through a garden holding a floral tote bag. Text overlays: \"The Artist Series with Anjelica Roselyn, Spring/Summer 26.\"\n\nAnjelica: Hi, I’m Anjelica Roselyn and I’m a fashion illustrator.\n\n[Visual Description]: Anjelica stands in her studio. Behind her is a mood board covered in vibrant fashion illustrations, fabric swatches, and color palettes.\n\nQuestion Overlay: How would you describe the collection in 3 words?\n\nAnjelica: I would describe the collection as fun, flirty, and feminine. Really great for Spring/Summer and so bright and colorful.\n\n[Visual Description]: Close-up shots of a pink and yellow floral tote bag and a smaller white handbag with a floral handle.\n\nQuestion Overlay: What story do you hope the prints tell?\n\nAnjelica: I’m really hoping these prints bring a lot of fun and whimsical energy to whoever wears them. Spring/Summer is my favorite season, so I really want the vibrancy to come through and I just want everyone to feel so fun and free wearing it.\n\n[Visual Description]: Anjelica sits in a director's chair outdoors, then gestures toward a white satchel featuring a butterfly and floral print.\n\nQuestion Overlay: How do you want women to feel when they wear these pieces?\n\nAnjelica: I want women to feel quite empowered when they wear these pieces. I want them to feel like, you know, they can put on these clothes, these scarves, these accessories, these bags and maybe hit the beach, and we just have such a great time.\n\n[Visual Description]: Montage of accessories: a colorful silk headscarf, a floral-faced watch, and a butterfly necklace.\n\nQuestion Overlay: How would you style the pieces into your current wardrobe?\n\nAnjelica: Well, for me, I’m all about more is more. So, I think put it all on, put all the earrings on, wear as many watches and bracelets and scarves as you want and just go crazy with it.\n\n[Visual Description]: Anjelica smiles and waves at the camera. The video concludes with the Anne Klein logo over a shimmering blue water background."
